<span id="freeTextContainer10750996528214752555">Having finished the second book in the series, I can say I’m really loving this foray into a mystery set during the reign of Henry II, our tour guide being Ariana Franklin. The protagonist is an antisocial (yet people loving) agnostic foreigner who is GAHHHHH educated. Sometimes I really dislike her sullenness and stubbornness, but she really is quite a detective, and we have multiple crimes and mysteries to unravel. <br/><br/>I love the characters Franklin has created, this historical murder mystery is a</span>
  <span id="freeText10750996528214752555" style="display:none">Having finished the second book in the series, I can say I’m really loving this foray into a mystery set during the reign of Henry II, our tour guide being Ariana Franklin. The protagonist is an antisocial (yet people loving) agnostic foreigner who is GAHHHHH educated. Sometimes I really dislike her sullenness and stubbornness, but she really is quite a detective, and we have multiple crimes and mysteries to unravel. <br /><br />I love the characters Franklin has created, this historical murder mystery is a very engaging read. I’m a fan ♥️</span>
