        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer476574425" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9725584117111425753">This series is working its way to becoming one of my favourites. In this one, Adelia is required to help determine the death and killer of King Henry II&apos;s fair Rosamund. I hesitate to call this historical fiction because it takes great liberties with the history. Shall we call it &quot;loosely historical&quot;? The author does take time to point out where she strays from what is known of the period. But the value in this book is the craftsmanship of storytelling that Ariana Franklin possessed. </span>
  <span id="freeText9725584117111425753" style="display:none">This series is working its way to becoming one of my favourites. In this one, Adelia is required to help determine the death and killer of King Henry II's fair Rosamund. I hesitate to call this historical fiction because it takes great liberties with the history. Shall we call it "loosely historical"? The author does take time to point out where she strays from what is known of the period. But the value in this book is the craftsmanship of storytelling that Ariana Franklin possessed. </span>
