    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_655119760" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/655119760" />
    <a title="Sara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/156639-sara"><img alt="Sara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1493660897p2/156639.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/655119760?book_show_action=true">Jun 30, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sara" href="/user/show/156639-sara">Sara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780425225745" href="/book/show/6066554-the-serpent-s-tale">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer655119760" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13418284700558114245">It wasn&apos;t terrible...in fact I&apos;m sure it was an accurate depiction of what things were like back then. But there were long stretches that were relatively uneventful bordering on boring. Also, the plot didn&apos;t seem very cohesive to me, and some of the main events were kind of glossed over so I often had to go reread passages to figure out what was going on or what had happened. Very little emotion evoked in this one. I didn&apos;t feel the fear, the disgust, the sadness, or the despair that should have</span>
  <span id="freeText13418284700558114245" style="display:none">It wasn't terrible...in fact I'm sure it was an accurate depiction of what things were like back then. But there were long stretches that were relatively uneventful bordering on boring. Also, the plot didn't seem very cohesive to me, and some of the main events were kind of glossed over so I often had to go reread passages to figure out what was going on or what had happened. Very little emotion evoked in this one. I didn't feel the fear, the disgust, the sadness, or the despair that should have been evoked. There were a few brief moments of passion, and one particularly lovely moment between Rowley and Adelia, but overall I lacked a connection to any of the characters. I remember really enjoying the first one, but it's been several years since I've read it. I will probably give the next one a try because I do really enjoy the setting and the concept of these novels. This one just fell a little short for me.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13418284700558114245" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


